tag.v: Illes Balears, Illes Balears, Spain, Europe
The island (with its surrounding islets) is not administratively subdivided into separate comarcas (level 7). It is administratively an insular council, assimilited to a comarca by itself.
There's no numeric admin_level defined for this type of administrative boundary, between levels 6 and 7.
This insular council was separated in 2007 from the insular council of Ibiza.
